What is non-blocking programming:-
Instead of putting a thread to sleep while waiting for an external system, the thread is immediately released to handle other tasks, and it
receives a notification or callback once the operation concludes.
How to achive non-blocking programmimg:-
1. Java NIO (New I/O) – System LevelIntroduced in Java 1.4, Java NIO shifts away from byte streams to buffer-oriented, channel-based data transfers.
2. Introduced in Java 8, CompletableFuture provides functional, event-driven methods to chain asynchronous tasks without calling blocking operations like .get() or .join()
3.Reactive Programming Frameworks – Architecture Level :-Spring WebFlux / Project Reactor: Instead of returning raw objects, endpoints return 
Mono<T> (0 or 1 item) or Flux<T> (0 to N items). The application acts as an event-driven loop.
4. Java 21 Virtual thread

